<br>
Hide alone is enough to hide from both living and undead.  Infact, any invisibility against living on a rogue is enough to be hidden from living and undead.  Invis vs Undead is still only undead.  All sneak adds is that something that sees invis has to be facing the rogue to see them, and they can move without breaking hide.<br>
<br>
When anybody hides, they will always see themselves as hidden whether they succeed or fail.  For non rogues to find out if they failed, they either have to con something living that doesn't see invis, or if they don't have see invisible, /target yourself, if you get yourself as a target you aren't hidden.  If you get that you can't see anyone with that name, you're hidden. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ferdynna@firionavie>Ferdynna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/4/03 10:27:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=152.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FD</span><hr size=1> Nope nope nope. Ever fought with a pet? A pet is an NPC, and as such has to follow certain rules that NPC mobs have to follow as well.<br>
